description:
&lt;p&gt;An excellent opportunity to develop as a Clinical Pharmacist in General Practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a group of GP Practices in Bath and North East Somerset but you will be employed by our local GP Federation Banes Enhanced Medical Services + (BEMS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will be provided with external support from the Centre for Pharmacy Postgraduate Education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require pharmacists with good clinical knowledge and self-motivation to develop themselves and support patients within a multi-professional team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will benefit from:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A joint NHS England, CCG &amp; General Practice initiative supported by a development programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work as part of a multi-professional team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A competitive salary – for a permanent contract&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively with local cross sector pharmacy professionals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independent prescribing qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPPE qualification (28 days study leave in the first 18 months)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aims&lt;/strong&gt;: to co-ordinate patient care working within a primary care setting, keeping patients well for longer and out of hospital by providing long term care in the community. This is a patient facing role and may involve conducting full medication reviews for patients from the following groups – housebound patients, patients in care homes, patients on complex multiple medications and patients with multiple morbidity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objectives:&lt;/strong&gt;to improve the quality of life and care for these patients, minimise unnecessary medicine-related hospital admissions, encourage ownership and self-management of conditions and to promote clinically effective prescribing resulting in improved value for the care systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to NHS Pension&lt;/p&gt;
